SIMPLE: worldly
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Worldly
<hw>World"ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>woroldlic</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Relating to the world; human; common; <as>as,
<ex>worldly</ex> maxims; <ex>worldly</ex> actions.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧I
thus neglecting <xex>worldly</xex> ends.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Many years it hath continued, standing by no other
<qex>worldly</qex> mean but that one only hand which erected it.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pertaining to this world or life, in
contradistinction from the life to come; secular; temporal; devoted to
this life and its enjoyments; bent on gain; <as>as, <ex>worldly</ex>
pleasures, affections, honor, lusts, men</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With his soul fled all my <qex>worldly</qex> solace.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Lay, as opposed to <xex>clerical</xex>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Worldly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Worldly
<hw>World"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>With relation to this life; in a
worldly manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Subverting <qex>worldly</qex> strong and <qex>worldly</qex>
wise⟦br⟧
By simply meek.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Worldly-minded</ent>⟦br⟧
